 #100DaysOfCode тАУ Day 92: Tackling Hardware Issues in Networking

Ever struggled with Power over Ethernet (PoE) or fiber optic transceivers? HereтАЩs what I learned today:
ЁЯФМ Power over Ethernet (PoE) Pitfalls:

    Not all PoE standards are equal! 802.3af (15W) тЙа 802.3at (25W) тЙа 802.3bt (71W).

    Pro Tip: Always check your switchтАЩs PoE budget before connecting devicesтАФexceeding it can crash your network!

ЁЯУб Fiber Optic Woes:

    Mismatched transceivers? Say hello to signal loss!

        Multimode fiber (850nm) тЙа Single-mode (1310/1550nm).

    Power budget math is key:
    Copy

    Received Power (dBm) = Transmitted Power - Cable Loss  

    If your received power < receiver sensitivity (e.g., -20dBm), expect errors!

Lesson: Hardware isnтАЩt "plug and play"тАФcompatibility and calculations matter!

